Netcare 911 airlifted a critically injured patient from a construction site in Fourways, Johannesburg, on Friday morning. Details of what happened are not known at present, but I Love Fourways on Twitter tweeted a video of the Netcare 911 helicopter taking off and said it was after an incident at Fourways Mall. Another Twitter user responded to the I Love Fourways tweet, saying a construction worker had fallen: @lindelwamrwata Construction worker fell. Fourways Mall to release report. &mdash; I Love Fourways (@ilovefourways) March 10, 2017 Fourways Mall has been under construction for more than a year. Chopper taking off after incident at Fourways Mall. pic.twitter.com/dd2FZit71e &mdash; I Love Fourways (@ilovefourways) March 10, 2017 Netcare 2 airlifted critically injured patient from a construction site in Fourways Gauteng @ewnupdates @JacaNews pic.twitter.com/npEV7djARp &mdash; Netcare911 (@Netcare911_sa) March 10, 2017 Details to follow as more information comes to light. Caxton News Service